===Verb===
{{en-verb|buys|buying|bought|bought|past_ptc2=boughten|past_ptc2_qual=rare, dialectal}}

# {{label|en|transitive}} To [[obtain]] (something) in [[exchange]] for money or goods
#: {{ux|en|I'm going to '''buy''' my father something nice for his birthday.}}
#* Benjamin Franklin
#*: '''Buy''' what thou hast no need of, and ere long thou wilt sell thy necessaries.
# {{label|en|transitive}} To obtain by some sacrifice.
#: {{ux|en|I've '''bought''' material comfort by foregoing my dreams.}}
#* Bible, Proverbs xxiii. 23
#*: '''Buy''' the truth and sell it not; also wisdom, and instruction, and understanding.
# {{label|en|transitive}} To [[bribe]].
#: {{ux|en|He tried to '''buy''' me with gifts, but I wouldn't give up my beliefs.}}
# {{label|en|transitive}} To be equivalent to in value.
#: {{ux|en|The dollar doesn't '''buy''' as much as it used to.}}
# {{label|en|transitive|informal}} to [[accept]] as true; to [[believe]]
#: {{ux|en|I'm not going to '''buy''' your stupid excuses anymore!}}
# {{label|en|intransitive}} To make a purchase or purchases, to [[treat]] (for a meal)
#: {{ux|en|She '''buys''' for Federated.}}
#: {{ux|en|Let's go out for dinner. I'm '''buying'''.}}
# {{label|en|poker slang|transitive}} To make a [[bluff]], usually a large one.
#: {{ux|en|Smith tried to '''buy''' the pot on the river with a huge bluff}}

